<br>
Please, tell/show me of ANY time where NB has either passed AoW or left him stand more than 24 hours and we were up for rotation?  <br>
<br>
To make it easy here is a link to the rotation history:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.jakefitch.com/rta/RotationDetail.asp?ID=5">www.jakefitch.com/rta/Rot...l.asp?ID=5</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
You keep going on about how Idol was up for a week?  When was this?  Who was up for him at the time?  And if he was up for that long why didn't YOU make an attempt at him?<br>
<br>
As for why I proposed waiting at least 2 spawnings between attemps was for simple curtosy for the guilds that are on the rotation.  Not just currently, but those that will be on the rotation in the future.  This isn't about VoF trying to get on the AoW rotation... this is about any guild trying to join any rotation where the mob despawns on failure.<br>
<br>
Lets say you do kill AoW next time, and get on the rotation.  Will you then want another guild despawning AoW every other spawn until they get on?  Would you want say Clan Bashemded poofing AoW every other week for 5 attempts until they finally win?  Or do you think it might be a bit nicer to the guilds on the rotation, to wait 2 spawnings before trying again.<br>
<br>
As for where 2 spawnsings came from, thats the minimum wait EVERY guild that is on AoW rotation currently between thier attempts (until recently).  <br>
<br>
BotS had to wait 2-3 weeks between thier first attempts because at that point Aow was triggered off Statues death (no Idol), so they could only attempt AoW on thier Statue kill.  (They did have a few attempts off other guilds Statue kills, but coordinating these was a very difficult process.)<br>
<br>
NB's first AoW attempt was after the Idol was added (the easy Idol), which we failed on (someone else killed Statue, but BotS hadn't gotten around to killing AoW yet).  Our second was 2 spawnings later on our Statue kill, and we won that time.<br>
<br>
SoT had a few failed attempts on thier Statue turns before the Idol was added.  Then when they did kill AoW after Idol was added, it was on thier Statue kill.<br>
<br>
When Tindi started trying for AoW is when the rule of only making attempts on your own Statue turn was first actually voiced.  I believe at this point there was 5 guilds on Statue rotation even.  (At least there was before Tindi successfully killed AoW.)<br>
<br>
